<subSubSection id="C33689E8FFB8FFBF99F6F958AF60B3B2" box="[189,1354,1720,1747]" pageId="5" pageNumber="113" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B93DA63FFB8FFBF99F6F958AF60B3B2" blockId="5.[136,1452,1720,1927]" box="[189,1354,1720,1747]" pageId="5" pageNumber="113">
<emphasis id="B9580671FFB8FFBF99F6F958AB4EB3B3" bold="true" box="[189,356,1721,1747]" pageId="5" pageNumber="113">Etymology:—</emphasis>
From the Latin for elegant, in reference to the handsome appearance of the large flowers.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33689E8FFB8FFBF99F6F93DAF69B2E6" pageId="5" pageNumber="113" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B93DA63FFB8FFBF99F6F93DA844B27B" blockId="5.[136,1452,1720,1927]" pageId="5" pageNumber="113">
<emphasis id="B9580671FFB8FFBF99F6F93DABCAB396" bold="true" box="[189,480,1756,1783]" pageId="5" pageNumber="113">Distribution and habitat</emphasis>
:—Known only from the 
<typeStatus id="549764C1FFB8FFBF9BB0F93CA901B397" box="[763,811,1757,1783]" pageId="5" pageNumber="113">type</typeStatus>
locality near Chaucha in 
<collectingRegion id="49E81481FFB8FFBF9D0CF93CAEBBB397" box="[1095,1169,1757,1783]" country="Ecuador" name="Azuay" pageId="5" pageNumber="113">Azuay</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F33B9AF3FFB8FFBF9DD7F93DAED1B396" box="[1180,1275,1756,1782]" name="Ecuador" pageId="5" pageNumber="113">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, where it grows epiphytically at an elevation around 
<specimenCount id="9D2A11EAFFB8FFBF9B6BF8E0A844B27B" box="[544,622,1793,1819]" pageId="5" pageNumber="113" type="generic">
<quantity id="4CD47786FFB8FFBF9B6BF8E0A840B27B" box="[544,618,1793,1819]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="113" unit="m" value="300.0">300 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B93DA63FFB8FFBF99F6F8C5AF69B2E6" blockId="5.[136,1452,1720,1927]" pageId="5" pageNumber="113">
<emphasis id="B9580671FFB8FFBF99F6F8C5AB9BB25F" bold="true" box="[189,433,1828,1855]" pageId="5" pageNumber="113">Conservation status:</emphasis>
— 
<materialsCitation id="3B44D03EFFB8FFBF9886F8C4AF14B2E6" collectionCode="DD, IUCN" country="Ecuador" location="This" municipality="Because" pageId="5" pageNumber="113" specimenCount="1">
To date, the species is known only from the 
<typeStatus id="549764C1FFB8FFBF9AE8F8C4A9F9B25F" box="[931,979,1829,1855]" pageId="5" pageNumber="113">type</typeStatus>
locality, which lies outside protected areas. 
<location id="8EF38CB8FFB8FFBF99C3F8A9AA90B202" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03856B75FFBEFFBF99C3FF15AF69B2E6:8EF38CB8FFB8FFBF99C3F8A9AA90B202" box="[136,186,1864,1890]" country="Ecuador" municipality="Because" name="This" pageId="5" pageNumber="113">This</location>
population is at risk due to deforestation. 
<collectingMunicipality id="6BF74019FFB8FFBF9BC6F8A8A8C0B203" box="[653,746,1865,1891]" pageId="5" pageNumber="113">Because</collectingMunicipality>
new localities will likely be found in poorly explored lowlands of western 
<collectingCountry id="F33B9AF3FFB8FFBF984FF88DAB49B2E6" box="[260,355,1900,1926]" name="Ecuador" pageId="5" pageNumber="113">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, we regard 
<taxonomicName id="4C2CA1E0FFB8FFBF98AEF88CA87CB2E6" authorityName="J. Ponert, M. Portilla &amp; Karremans" authorityYear="2021" box="[485,598,1900,1926]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Pabstiella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="elegans">
<emphasis id="B9580671FFB8FFBF98AEF88CA87CB2E6" box="[485,598,1900,1926]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="113">P. elegans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as data deficient (
<collectionCode id="ED3D42A6FFB8FFBF9A69F88CA967B2E7" box="[802,845,1901,1927]" country="India" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13033" name="Forest Research Institute, Indian Council of Forestry Research and Education" pageId="5" pageNumber="113" type="Herbarium">DD</collectionCode>
) according to the 
<collectionCode id="ED3D42A6FFB8FFBF9D5CF88CAE71B2E7" box="[1047,1115,1901,1927]" pageId="5" pageNumber="113">IUCN</collectionCode>
Red List categories
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
